Abstract = {{Previous work has established that the localized regime of wave
   transport in open media is characterized by a position-dependent
   diffusion coefficient. In this work we study how the concept of
   position-dependent diffusion affects the delay time, the transverse
   confinement, the coherent backscattering, and the time reversal of
   waves. Definitions of energy transport velocity of localized waves are
   proposed. We start with a phenomenological model of radiative transfer
   and then present a novel perturbational approach based on the
   self-consistent theory of localization. The latter allows us to obtain
   results relevant for realistic experiments in disordered quasi-1D wave
   guides and 3D slabs.}},
