Abstract = {{This paper describes how coherent backscattering is altered by an
   external magnetic field. In the theory presented, magneto-optical
   effects occur inside Mie scatterers embedded in a nonmagnetic medium.
   Unlike previous theories based on pointlike scatterers, the decrease of
   coherent backscattering is obtained in a leading order of the magnetic
   field using rigorous Mie theory. This decrease is strongly enhanced in
   the proximity of resonances, which cause the path length of the wave
   inside a scatterer to be increased. Also presented is an analysis of the
   shape of the backscattering cone in a magnetic field.}},
